gomodel:SYNGO_3646  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Stereotyped developmental elimination of synapses in the Caenorhabditis elegans\nhermaphrodite-specific motor neuron (HSNL) is mediated by an E3 ubiquitin ligase, a Skp1-cullin-F-box (SCF) complex composed of SKR-1 (SKP1 homolog) and the F-box protein SEL-10. Figure 3:more skr-1 RNAi-treated animals than control animals had SNB-1::egfp labeled synapses in the secondary synapse region (SSR, (Fig. 3, B and C) suggesting that SKR1 is necessary for proper synapse elimination. Figure 4E, over expression of SKR-1 results in reduced synapse numbers in primary synapse region and SSR showing that SKR-1 is rate-limiting for synapse elimination.. Experimental description: Abstract: Caenorhabditis elegans hermaphrodite-specificmotor neuron (HSNL)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3646" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6239" .

